[30;1m34 | [0m[35m   is a doubly-whammy principle-of-least-astonishment violation: (1) users[0m
[30;1m35 | [0m[35m   are likely to accidentally commit the "staged" changes, re-introducing the[0m

[30;1m38 | [0m[35m   Fixing these two glaring problems not only makes --no-blob-protection[0m
[30;1m39 | [0m[35m   safe to recommend, it makes it safe to make it the default.)[0m

[30;1m256 | [0m[35m[0m

[30;1m259 | [0m[35mnew commit IDs.  Often they do get the same new commit IDs, but[0m

[30;1m231 | [0m[35mYou are probably looking for `git rebase`.  `git rebase` operates on the[0m
[30;1m232 | [0m[35mdifference between commits ("diff"), allowing you to e.g. drop or modify[0m

  Severity: [36mModerate[0m, Confidence: [36mLow[0m
  Filename: [33m/git_filter_repo-2.47.0/Documentation/FAQ.md[0m
   Pattern: [32m\s(apt|apt\-get|aria2c|arp|ash|awk|base64|bash|bpftrace|busybox|cat|chmod|chown|cp|cpan|cpulimit|crontab|csh|curl|cut|dash|dd|diff|dmesg|dmsetup|dnf|docker|dpkg|easy_install|ed|emacs|env|expand|expect|facter|find|finger|flock|fmt|ftp|gawk|gdb|gimp|git|grep|head|iftop|ionice|ip|irb|jjs|journalctl|jrunscript|ksh|ld\.so|ldconfig|logsave|ltrace|lua|mail|mawk|mount|mtr|mv|mysql|nano|nawk|nc|nice|nl|nmap|node|od|openssl|perl|pg|php|pic|pico|pip|puppet|readelf|red|rlogin|rlwrap|rpm|rpmquery|rsync|ruby|run\-mailcap|run\-parts|rvim|scp|screen|script|sed|service|setarch|sftp|shuf|smbclient|socat|sort|sqlite3|ssh|start\-stop\-daemon|stdbuf|strace|systemctl|tail|tar|taskset|tclsh|tcpdump|tee|telnet|tftp|time|timeout|tmux|top|ul|unexpand|uniq|unshare|vi|vim|watch|wget|whois|wish|xargs|xxd|yum|zsh|zypper)\s[0m
[30;1m45 | [0m[35mthat commit's hash must change.  Further, since that commit will have a[0m
[30;1m46 | [0m[35mnew hash, any other commit with that commit as a parent will need to[0m
[30;1m47 | [0m[35mhave a new hash.  That will need to chain all the way to the most recent[0m
[30;1m48 | [0m[35mcommits in history.  This is fundamental to Git and there is nothing you[0m
[30;1m49 | [0m[35mcan do to change this.[0m

[30;1m77 | [0m[35mis all contained in a single-file python script named[0m
[30;1m78 | [0m[35m`git-filter-repo`, which was done to make installation for basic use[0m
[30;1m79 | [0m[35mon many systems trivial: just place that one file into your $PATH.[0m
